WEBVTT

00:01.646 --> 00:02.991
<i>Previously on Nashville...</i>

00:02.992 --> 00:04.567
Have you worked as a backup singer before?

00:04.568 --> 00:06.236
I can sing. I can really sing.

00:06.587 --> 00:08.093
You've been given a voice, girl.

00:08.095 --> 00:09.861
Just keep singing what you
believe in. You're gonna be fine.

00:09.862 --> 00:12.229
I also wanna thank my manager,

00:12.230 --> 00:13.968
for sticking by me all these years.

00:13.969 --> 00:14.850
We're dropping you.

00:14.851 --> 00:16.360
You're no longer an Edgehill artist.

00:16.361 --> 00:18.238
Scarlett O'Connor, meet Liam McGuinnis.

00:18.239 --> 00:19.168
Y'all have fun.

00:20.037 --> 00:23.170
Did you try to murder
the father of my children?

00:23.171 --> 00:25.445
As far as I'm concerned,
both my parents are dead.

00:25.446 --> 00:26.685
Lamar?

00:26.686 --> 00:27.604
Help me.

00:28.414 --> 00:29.786
[Grunting]

00:31.830 --> 00:34.375
♪ I'm not under your spell ♪

00:34.376 --> 00:37.287
♪ I'm not under your spell ♪

00:37.288 --> 00:40.353
♪ I'm not under your spell ♪

00:40.354 --> 00:45.427
♪ I'm not under
your spe-e-ll ♪

00:45.956 --> 00:47.322
[cellphone buzzing]

00:47.323 --> 00:51.586
♪ ooh, ooh ♪

00:52.735 --> 00:54.159
♪ ooh ♪

00:54.477 --> 00:55.999
[buzzing continues]

00:56.314 --> 00:57.549
[Buzzing stops]

01:00.398 --> 01:02.298
Well? What do you think?

01:02.299 --> 01:04.114
I think it's amazing.

01:04.824 --> 01:05.937
[Chuckles] It's amazing!

01:05.938 --> 01:06.821
Thank you.

01:06.822 --> 01:08.287
Thought you were gonna
hate it for some reason.

01:08.288 --> 01:10.251
Why would I hate that? I love it.

01:10.252 --> 01:12.058
It's... it's so... it's beautiful.

01:12.059 --> 01:14.614
It's moving and... and raw and emotional.

01:14.615 --> 01:16.602
You really... you dug
deep for that one, girl.

01:16.603 --> 01:18.024
And the mix... I love the mix.

01:18.025 --> 01:19.793
It... it feels like it's right in my ear.

01:19.794 --> 01:21.006
- Thanks. Thanks.
- Yeah.

01:21.007 --> 01:22.172
You didn't doubt me, did you?

01:22.518 --> 01:23.577
How could I ever doubt you?

01:24.142 --> 01:25.476
Well, all right, I mean,

01:25.477 --> 01:27.121
y'all got everything under control here,

01:27.122 --> 01:30.464
so I'm just gonna go deal with a
couple other things [Cellphone buzzing]

01:30.465 --> 01:32.669
- And... and leave you to it.
- Thank you.

01:32.670 --> 01:33.816
Okay. [Chuckles]

01:33.817 --> 01:35.078
- Great work.
- Thanks.

01:35.079 --> 01:36.063
Okay.

01:36.916 --> 01:37.915
Is everything okay?

01:39.347 --> 01:41.699
Yeah. Why?

01:42.283 --> 01:43.685
I heard your dad is out.

01:44.045 --> 01:45.509
That must be a relief.

01:45.510 --> 01:48.576
Let's just say I'm happy to
be focusing on work right now.

01:49.290 --> 01:51.471
If you need me, um, I'm here.

01:51.472 --> 01:54.977
Honestly, what you're doing with
Scarlett is the biggest help.

01:54.978 --> 01:56.501
I appreciate it so much.

01:57.462 --> 01:59.963
You know I've invested
everything in that girl.

01:59.964 --> 02:00.849
Yeah.

02:00.850 --> 02:02.131
This album has to be great.

02:03.204 --> 02:04.384
How are you and Luke?

02:04.722 --> 02:05.651
We're good.

02:05.652 --> 02:06.797
Oh. Just "good"?

02:07.128 --> 02:08.767
Go work. Make it great.

02:08.768 --> 02:09.598
Okay.

02:09.941 --> 02:13.867
♪ Oh, so don't put dirt
on my grave just yet ♪

02:13.868 --> 02:15.211
♪ Grave just yet ♪

02:15.212 --> 02:16.016
♪ No ♪

02:16.017 --> 02:19.385
♪ Don't put dirt on my grave just yet ♪

02:19.991 --> 02:21.150
♪ No ♪

02:21.665 --> 02:26.617
♪ Don't put dirt on my grave just yet ♪

02:26.618 --> 02:27.503
Well?

02:29.134 --> 02:30.655
Uh, it's...

02:32.417 --> 02:34.161
"Perfect" is the wrong word.

02:34.162 --> 02:36.647
What is a word that's
better than "perfect"?

02:36.648 --> 02:37.838
I love it.

02:38.538 --> 02:40.337
Are you k... I don't know how you did it,

02:40.885 --> 02:44.174
but it feels like you put my soul in there.

02:44.175 --> 02:45.225
I'm glad you like it.

02:45.565 --> 02:46.554
[Sighs]

02:46.555 --> 02:48.163
It's too bad nobody'll ever hear it.

02:48.164 --> 02:49.138
Why not?

02:50.133 --> 02:51.715
Well, 'cause Jeff Fordham dropped me,

02:52.141 --> 02:55.134
and no other label in this
city will touch me, remember?

02:55.135 --> 02:56.777
Yeah, but you have other
people in your corner.

02:56.778 --> 02:58.268
You don't count.

02:58.269 --> 03:00.649
I'm gonna not take that personally.

03:00.650 --> 03:02.948
And besides, I'm not talking about me.

03:03.451 --> 03:05.506
I'm talking about Ken Inman.

03:05.507 --> 03:06.706
Wait... Ken Inman,

03:06.707 --> 03:08.724
<i>the New York Times music critic, Ken...</i>

03:08.725 --> 03:11.149
Is there another one that would
be relevant to this conversation?

03:11.150 --> 03:13.087
No. What'd he say?

03:13.088 --> 03:14.907
Does this mean you're lifting
your own media blackout?

03:14.908 --> 03:16.377
- Shut up. Tell me.
- All right.

03:16.683 --> 03:20.226
Apparently, Inman watched
your induction performance

03:20.227 --> 03:21.628
on the Opry website.

03:22.365 --> 03:23.202
You ready?

03:23.914 --> 03:24.996
Check it out.

03:25.983 --> 03:28.755
"Juliette Barnes is best
known for spangled hot pants

03:28.756 --> 03:31.946
and, of course, her many
tabloid appearances."

03:31.947 --> 03:33.625
Just... it gets better. Keep going.

03:34.350 --> 03:39.048
"But her brave, rebellious,
and eye-opening performance

03:39.049 --> 03:41.560
"of 'Don't put Dirt on my Grave Just Yet'

03:41.561 --> 03:43.584
"at her induction into the Grand Ole Opry

03:43.585 --> 03:46.171
"proves that Barnes has a deeper spring

03:46.172 --> 03:47.430
"and is an artist with music

03:47.431 --> 03:50.215
worthy of serious
consideration and respect."

03:52.432 --> 03:55.508
<i>The New York Times just
called you a serious artist.</i>

03:55.509 --> 03:58.150
Yeah, it only took me trashing
my career for this to happen,

03:58.151 --> 04:01.679
and it's great, but...

04:01.680 --> 04:03.659
You do know that you're
the only person in Nashville

04:03.660 --> 04:05.189
<i>who reads the New York Times?</i>

04:05.190 --> 04:08.519
Every other paper is literally
putting dirt on my grave.

04:08.520 --> 04:11.813
Can you just bask in the glow of good news

04:11.814 --> 04:13.244
[sighs] For like two minutes?

04:13.245 --> 04:14.238
No.

04:14.611 --> 04:16.375
<i>But I can bask in you.</i>

04:21.168 --> 04:22.221
Deacon: Don't even worry about it.

04:22.222 --> 04:24.066
Look, I totally understand,
man. This is very last-minute.

04:24.067 --> 04:25.764
Just got it from my booking agent myself.

04:25.765 --> 04:27.302
I figured you'd be busy.

04:27.303 --> 04:29.261
All right. All right. Thanks, Chuck.

04:29.836 --> 04:30.854
[Cellphone beeps] [Sighs]

04:30.855 --> 04:32.047
No luck?

04:32.442 --> 04:35.034
I can't even get a damn
drummer, let alone a whole band.

04:35.035 --> 04:36.193
Thank you.

04:36.194 --> 04:37.716
Hey, why don't you ask Scarlett?

04:37.717 --> 04:39.210
<i>Maybe her band could back you up.</i>

04:39.211 --> 04:40.315
Honey, those guys are pros.

04:40.316 --> 04:42.985
They don't want to drive an hour
to play some dinky little dive.

04:42.986 --> 04:45.231
So why are you? You sold
out the Bluebird last night.

04:45.232 --> 04:46.236
You're playing there again tomorrow.

04:46.237 --> 04:47.239
I'm just not in a position

04:47.240 --> 04:48.926
to be turning down gigs
right now, you know?

04:48.927 --> 04:52.543
I just... Need to find
some like-minded suckers

04:52.544 --> 04:54.880
willing to play for
warm beer and cold pizza.

04:56.320 --> 04:57.251
[Giggles]

04:58.918 --> 05:00.150
Glenn: Juliette?

05:00.151 --> 05:01.351
[Knock on door]

05:01.352 --> 05:02.456
Who's that?

05:02.457 --> 05:03.769
Juliette?

05:04.254 --> 05:06.239
Does he always just
show up without calling?

05:06.240 --> 05:07.876
<i>Everybody does.</i>

05:07.877 --> 05:08.858
I don't...

05:08.859 --> 05:10.352
Juliette, why aren't you answering my...

05:10.353 --> 05:11.554
Oh, my God! Excuse me.

05:11.555 --> 05:13.019
I'm so sorry. I didn't know you two were...

05:13.020 --> 05:15.507
Glenn! Why aren't you on vacation?!

05:15.508 --> 05:16.232
I-I...

05:16.233 --> 05:18.311
I told you to! I didn't
want to be disturbed!

05:18.312 --> 05:19.365
I know, but this can't wait.

05:19.366 --> 05:21.785
<i>Look, there's a piece in the
New York Times by Ken Inman.</i>

05:21.786 --> 05:24.274
I know. I know. Avery told me already.

05:24.275 --> 05:26.546
Yeah, yeah, but you don't
know that Howie V read it,

05:26.547 --> 05:28.274
and... and he saw the Opry website video.

05:28.275 --> 05:29.325
He wants to meet you.

05:29.326 --> 05:32.997
Like 12 Grammys and 17
VMAs super-producer Howie V?

05:32.998 --> 05:35.116
Exactly. He's sending his jet for you.

05:35.117 --> 05:36.238
It took off two hours ago,

05:36.239 --> 05:37.974
which you would know if you
would have returned my calls,

05:37.975 --> 05:39.238
but you guys were... you know.

05:39.239 --> 05:40.473
Come on! Get dressed! Get dressed.

05:40.474 --> 05:41.511
We're going to L.A.

05:41.512 --> 05:44.448
<i>I'm sorry...  we're going to
L.A. the meeting's for you.</i>

05:44.449 --> 05:46.537
He just produced an
amazing version of the song.

05:46.538 --> 05:49.097
Hey, hey, hey, it's okay.
It's all right. I got work.

05:49.098 --> 05:50.163
Next time.

05:50.164 --> 05:51.172
Fine.

05:51.173 --> 05:53.227
Send Howie V Avery's mix of the song,

05:53.228 --> 05:55.397
because if he thinks
that Opry video was good,

05:55.398 --> 05:57.027
this is gonna blow his mind.

05:57.028 --> 05:57.954
Okay.

05:59.655 --> 06:00.288
[Sighs]

06:00.715 --> 06:01.803
[Sighs]

06:01.804 --> 06:03.311
Oh, he's seen worse.

06:03.784 --> 06:05.080
Rayna: So, we'll just update the website

06:05.081 --> 06:07.080
to say "Scarlett O'Connor is taking a break

06:07.081 --> 06:08.278
"from the Luke Wheeler tour

06:08.665 --> 06:12.021
"to record with legendary
producer Liam McGuinnis,

06:12.022 --> 06:14.842
who also produced Rayna's
most recent album."

06:15.271 --> 06:15.862
- I like that one.
- Hey, Rayna?

06:17.168 --> 06:18.120
Hey.

06:18.121 --> 06:19.238
Listen, I've been trying
to reach you for hours.

06:19.239 --> 06:21.215
I know. I'm sorry. I-I-I
wanted to call you back.

06:21.216 --> 06:22.975
I just... I wanted to have a quiet moment,

06:22.976 --> 06:24.162
and I just had a crazy morning.

06:24.632 --> 06:25.482
What's going on?

06:26.722 --> 06:27.533
[Exhales deeply]

06:27.534 --> 06:28.589
I'm sorry, Rayna.

06:28.590 --> 06:30.497
I don't... I don't know
how to say this, but...

06:32.252 --> 06:33.995
Lamar passed away this morning.

06:34.575 --> 06:35.524
What?

06:35.525 --> 06:37.756
Yeah. He had a heart attack in my office.

06:38.245 --> 06:39.221
I'm sorry.

06:39.222 --> 06:41.196
It just... it happened so fast.

06:41.197 --> 06:43.436
He came storming in, all worked up,

06:43.437 --> 06:45.694
accusing me of testifying against him.

06:45.695 --> 06:47.399
I tried to explain, get him to calm down,

06:48.201 --> 06:49.847
and next thing I know,
he's grabbing his chest,

06:49.848 --> 06:51.129
and he's on the ground, and I...

06:51.740 --> 06:53.298
you know, I shouted for help,

06:53.299 --> 06:55.189
but then by the time
the paramedics got there,

06:55.190 --> 06:56.468
he was gone.

06:59.798 --> 07:00.871
Does Tandy know?

07:00.872 --> 07:02.156
No.

07:02.157 --> 07:03.514
I wanted to tell you first.

07:05.187 --> 07:06.442
The police and the paramedics...

07:06.443 --> 07:07.918
they said that they would
keep this under wraps

07:07.919 --> 07:09.679
until we can make an official statement.

07:10.047 --> 07:11.028
Maddie: Dad?

07:13.711 --> 07:15.202
What's wrong?

07:17.486 --> 07:25.546
Synced and corrected by Nantinha
~ www.addic7ed.com ~

07:32.825 --> 07:35.056
You see, your grandpa had a weak heart,

07:35.057 --> 07:38.013
and he never really recovered
from his first heart attack.

07:38.014 --> 07:39.590
It just doesn't make any sense.

07:40.271 --> 07:41.773
We were right here with him,

07:41.774 --> 07:44.327
singing and laughing, like a minute ago.

07:44.328 --> 07:46.742
I know, honey, but he'd been through a lot,

07:46.743 --> 07:48.346
and the stress was just too much for him.

07:49.344 --> 07:51.339
[Voice breaking] He was so
happy to be home with us.

07:51.649 --> 07:53.041
He wasn't stressed.

07:54.026 --> 07:55.174
Right, mom?

07:55.646 --> 07:58.545
These things are just...
Hard to understand.

07:58.546 --> 07:59.394
Right.

07:59.395 --> 08:00.795
We can be thankful that he got to spend

08:00.796 --> 08:03.209
one of his last days with
the people that he loved.

08:03.210 --> 08:04.963
[Voice breaking] Does
this mean he's in heaven?

08:05.949 --> 08:07.519
Yes, sweetheart.

08:07.520 --> 08:10.153
He's, uh... He's with your grandma now.

08:10.154 --> 08:12.570
It's not just about mixing
the right ingredients.

08:12.571 --> 08:13.723
You got to make sure

08:13.724 --> 08:16.044
that the spirits are guiding the reaction.

08:16.045 --> 08:18.784
Hey, make sure that Sasha and
Malia got those Rihanna tickets.

08:18.785 --> 08:19.286
Woman: Okay.

08:19.287 --> 08:22.066
And right now, girl, you
are in the sweet spot.

08:22.067 --> 08:23.760
The whole world's watching you,

08:23.761 --> 08:25.559
wondering who you're gonna dance with

08:25.560 --> 08:28.041
now that you broke up with country music.

08:28.365 --> 08:29.965
Uh, well, in all fairness,

08:29.966 --> 08:31.738
<i>country music kind of broke up with me.</i>

08:31.739 --> 08:32.803
Ah! Even better.

08:33.424 --> 08:36.006
'Cause your rebound needs
to be bigger and bolder.

08:36.517 --> 08:37.427
Please.

08:38.034 --> 08:40.879
Let those country folks
cry into their boots

08:40.880 --> 08:44.236
because they didn't
realize the absolute goddess

08:44.238 --> 08:45.588
in their midst.

08:45.589 --> 08:47.086
[Chuckling] I don't know about "goddess."

08:47.087 --> 08:49.012
No earthly creature could have written

08:49.013 --> 08:51.124
"don't put dirt on my grave just yet."

08:51.125 --> 08:52.713
You have to have been reincarnated, what...

08:52.714 --> 08:55.201
a hundred times... to
have enough pain and anger

08:55.202 --> 08:56.434
to tell that story.

08:56.735 --> 08:57.731
Am I right? Am I right?

08:58.033 --> 08:59.058
Thank you.

08:59.059 --> 08:59.954
[Chuckles]

08:59.955 --> 09:02.670
I actually co-wrote it
with, uh, Avery Barkley.

09:02.671 --> 09:04.907
He did the mix that
we... you sent it to him?

09:04.908 --> 09:05.549
- Oh, yeah.
- Did you hear it?

09:05.550 --> 09:06.719
Yeah, yeah. I did. I did.

09:06.720 --> 09:08.999
So, here's what I'm thinking...
we get you in the studio.

09:09.000 --> 09:11.489
I show you that bigger is
definitely better... my treat.

09:11.490 --> 09:13.156
My treat. What do you say?

09:13.157 --> 09:14.796
Do you want to do
something historic with me?

09:14.797 --> 09:16.789
When do we start? [Chuckles]

09:20.220 --> 09:24.708
♪ I'm old enough to know that
I'm too young to know a thing ♪

09:24.709 --> 09:26.077
♪ But I see what I see ♪

09:26.078 --> 09:31.056
♪ And then you see
everything I'll ever need ♪

09:33.725 --> 09:38.411
♪ Well, I've met a lot of faces,
and I know a lot of names ♪

09:38.412 --> 09:42.606
♪ But every one I've come across
has all been just the same ♪

09:42.607 --> 09:45.573
♪ But that all changed ♪

09:47.092 --> 09:51.181
♪ That all changed ♪

09:51.793 --> 09:53.976
♪ Under the downtown neon lights ♪

09:54.492 --> 09:56.697
♪ That's where you caught my eye ♪

09:56.698 --> 09:58.837
♪ You got me all worked up ♪

09:58.838 --> 10:00.915
♪ I ain't leaving without your love ♪

10:01.230 --> 10:03.722
♪ It's obvious we both know ♪

10:03.723 --> 10:05.990
♪ This won't end tomorrow ♪

10:05.991 --> 10:07.853
♪ Tonight ain't long enough ♪

10:07.854 --> 10:10.153
♪ I ain't leaving without your love ♪

10:10.154 --> 10:12.281
♪ No, tonight ain't long enough ♪

10:12.282 --> 10:14.548
♪ I ain't leaving without your love ♪

10:14.549 --> 10:16.906
♪ Yeah ♪
♪ tonight
ain't long enough ♪

10:16.907 --> 10:19.128
♪ I ain't leaving without your love ♪

10:19.129 --> 10:22.052
♪ I ain't leaving without your love ♪

10:23.203 --> 10:24.729
[Clapping]

10:24.730 --> 10:25.620
Whoo.

10:25.621 --> 10:26.542
- Hey!
- Deacon.

10:26.543 --> 10:27.636
Sorry to barge right in.

10:27.637 --> 10:29.291
I just wanted to see what I was hearing.

10:29.292 --> 10:30.640
- That was killer.
- Thanks.

10:30.641 --> 10:32.286
I've been trying to reach both
of you on the phone all day.

10:32.287 --> 10:33.450
I can see why I couldn't.

10:33.451 --> 10:35.722
Oh, we were just working out
the kinks on a new song of mine.

10:35.723 --> 10:36.851
Well, I didn't hear no kinks.

10:36.852 --> 10:38.092
- So, what's up?
- You know what?

10:38.093 --> 10:39.519
I'm supposed to be playing a couple songs

10:39.520 --> 10:41.020
at this place right
outside of town tonight,

10:41.021 --> 10:42.531
and I was trying to get a band earlier.

10:42.532 --> 10:43.518
At this point, I'd just settle

10:43.519 --> 10:44.747
for a guitar player to help me out.

10:44.748 --> 10:46.313
Uh, either one of you able to,

10:46.314 --> 10:48.594
uh, do a gig for little to no money?

10:48.595 --> 10:49.280
[Chuckles]

10:49.281 --> 10:50.291
You don't have to pay me a dime.

10:50.292 --> 10:51.556
I'd love to play a gig with you.

10:51.557 --> 10:52.421
- You serious?
- Yeah.

10:52.732 --> 10:53.595
Thank you.

10:53.596 --> 10:54.950
- Hey, I can play drums.
- That'd be great,

10:54.951 --> 10:56.808
but I don't really have a bass
player at this point, so...

10:56.809 --> 10:58.151
Avery: I-I can find a bass player.

10:58.152 --> 10:59.591
- You sure?
- Yeah. I mean, you got charts?

10:59.592 --> 11:00.925
- Yeah, I got charts. Yeah.
- All right, yeah, we're good.

11:00.926 --> 11:04.191
Hey, I'd be happy to sing backup
if you think it would help.

11:04.192 --> 11:04.980
Really?

11:05.330 --> 11:07.923
Yeah, I mean, I do sing.

11:07.924 --> 11:09.673
Well, yeah. It's just... it's a real gig.

11:09.674 --> 11:11.172
You don't want me to?

11:11.173 --> 11:12.108
Of course I do.

11:12.109 --> 11:14.343
Hey, Gun, I heard that girl sing.

11:14.945 --> 11:15.955
You're in.

11:15.956 --> 11:16.968
I'll be right back.

11:17.717 --> 11:19.036
Would you just let them know

11:19.037 --> 11:21.857
that, um, we've had a family emergency,

11:21.858 --> 11:24.062
and as soon as I come up for air again,

11:24.063 --> 11:26.088
I'll put it back on the books for sure.

11:26.089 --> 11:27.405
I appreciate you.

11:27.406 --> 11:28.914
Thank you. Thank you so much.

11:28.915 --> 11:29.880
Bye-bye.

11:31.988 --> 11:33.244
I was surprised you called.

11:36.208 --> 11:37.469
I hadn't planned to.

11:38.013 --> 11:39.086
I'm sorry.

11:40.417 --> 11:42.014
I-I don't know what else to say.

11:42.015 --> 11:44.256
I really, truly am sorry.

11:44.257 --> 11:45.730
Daddy's dead.

11:45.731 --> 11:46.897
What?

11:47.360 --> 11:49.092
He had another heart attack.

11:49.093 --> 11:50.493
[Voice breaking] What?

11:52.242 --> 11:54.070
- Yeah.
- No, no, no, no.

11:54.071 --> 11:55.416
- Yeah, he's gone.
- No.

11:55.869 --> 11:58.307
I started the ball rolling
on the funeral arrangements...

11:58.308 --> 11:59.974
made some calls, and, you know,

11:59.975 --> 12:03.557
I think we'll just do
something real simple, private.

12:04.485 --> 12:05.561
Nothing too grand.

12:05.562 --> 12:07.102
[Sobbing]

12:07.553 --> 12:08.666
Oh, please, Tandy.

12:09.478 --> 12:10.861
He was a murderer.

12:11.380 --> 12:12.803
Isn't that what you said?

12:13.980 --> 12:15.036
What?

12:15.435 --> 12:16.895
[Sobbing]

12:17.373 --> 12:18.774
[Indistinct conversations]

12:25.044 --> 12:26.696
[Camera shutters clicking]

12:29.766 --> 12:33.258
Earlier today, Lamar Wyatt,
my former father-in-law,

12:33.259 --> 12:35.498
suffered a massive heart
attack in my office.

12:35.499 --> 12:37.591
[Reporters gasp]
Nashville's finest paramedics

12:37.592 --> 12:39.303
took every measure to revive him,

12:39.774 --> 12:42.803
but after being transferred
to Vanderbilt Medical,

12:42.804 --> 12:45.341
he was pronounced dead at 11:55 A.M.

12:45.785 --> 12:48.023
My daughters, Maddie and Daphne Conrad,

12:48.024 --> 12:50.314
have lost a loving grandfather.

12:51.036 --> 12:53.194
Rayna Jaymes and her sister, Tandy Hampton,

12:53.195 --> 12:56.316
have lost a father, and the
city has lost a towering figure,

12:56.317 --> 12:58.005
one of its leading patrons.

12:58.006 --> 12:59.872
[Reporters shouting questions]

12:59.873 --> 13:01.941
Mayor, what about the recent
controversy regarding...

13:01.942 --> 13:03.560
Lamar Wyatt and I...

13:03.561 --> 13:05.386
well, we had our
differences over the years.

13:05.907 --> 13:09.467
But I also wouldn't be where I
am today without his guidance.

13:10.176 --> 13:12.980
He'll be remembered as a
pillar of Nashville society,

13:12.981 --> 13:14.394
and deservedly so.

13:15.248 --> 13:16.652
May he rest in peace.

13:16.653 --> 13:18.371
Thank you. [Reporters shouting questions]

13:18.372 --> 13:19.641
One song down.

13:19.642 --> 13:20.636
[Chuckles]

13:20.637 --> 13:21.872
10 more to go.

13:21.873 --> 13:23.072
Cheers.

13:24.945 --> 13:27.305
You, uh, think we're actually
gonna get this thing finished

13:27.306 --> 13:29.247
before you go off...
Wherever it is you're going?

13:29.248 --> 13:31.583
Tokyo... for two weeks.

13:31.584 --> 13:32.697
And then off to Ireland

13:32.698 --> 13:34.701
to record this new Celtic rock band.

13:34.702 --> 13:35.647
Then Prague.

13:35.648 --> 13:37.577
Yeah, we got to... we got
to hurry it up around here.

13:37.578 --> 13:39.545
[Chuckles] Okay, your life
sounds kind of amazing.

13:39.546 --> 13:40.681
Sometimes.

13:40.682 --> 13:42.183
It's a lot of work, a lot of travel,

13:42.184 --> 13:43.736
and not a lot of time for anything else.

13:43.737 --> 13:44.972
- Mm.
- Or anyone.

13:45.349 --> 13:47.063
I guess that's the downside to it.

13:47.064 --> 13:49.364
Yeah, well, this life can
be cruel to relationships.

13:50.155 --> 13:53.100
- Mm-hmm. - It gets
lonely sometimes.

13:53.101 --> 13:54.637
Oh, come on, you're too cool to be lonely.

13:54.638 --> 13:55.476
Don't you have a house

13:55.477 --> 13:56.789
on, like, three different
continents or something?

13:56.790 --> 13:59.828
Yep. And nobody's waiting
for me in any of them.

14:01.335 --> 14:02.946
H-how do you cope with that part?

14:02.947 --> 14:04.918
Work more, play more, record more.

14:05.862 --> 14:07.339
Not your own stuff, though.

14:07.340 --> 14:09.215
Hasn't it been a while
since you put anything out?

14:09.216 --> 14:13.147
To be honest, I'm...
I-I feel kind of stuck.

14:13.596 --> 14:16.073
Spending so much time working
on the other people's music...

14:16.074 --> 14:18.607
I can't really wrap my head around my own.

14:18.608 --> 14:20.903
Which I'm probably doing
it on purpose, you know?

14:20.904 --> 14:22.776
I'm trying to hide from my own music.

14:22.777 --> 14:23.866
You know what I mean?

14:23.867 --> 14:25.604
Yes. I do.

14:25.605 --> 14:26.594
[Chuckles]

14:26.595 --> 14:27.931
Should we get another round?

14:28.687 --> 14:30.282
Yeah. Thanks.

14:31.787 --> 14:32.813
[Knock on door]

14:35.637 --> 14:36.676
Hi.

14:36.677 --> 14:37.817
Hi.

14:38.780 --> 14:41.343
That was a nice speech
you gave about Lamar.

14:41.344 --> 14:43.185
Fulfilling my mayoral duties.

14:43.186 --> 14:45.565
And, you know, trying to be a good dad.

14:45.566 --> 14:46.703
Meaning?

14:46.704 --> 14:48.267
I-I know it won't bring Peggy back,

14:48.268 --> 14:50.839
but if I just keep letting
all that ugliness in,

14:50.840 --> 14:52.809
I'm not gonna have anything
left for my girls, so...

14:52.810 --> 14:56.280
Well, that is incredibly
healthy and mature.

14:56.281 --> 14:58.485
Well, life's too short
to hold on to resentment.

14:59.473 --> 15:01.843
It's toxic. Isn't that what you told me?

15:02.153 --> 15:03.647
I didn't know you were listening.

15:04.123 --> 15:05.304
I was.

15:06.757 --> 15:08.531
Look, I know I'm...

15:08.532 --> 15:10.430
I'm not supposed to actually
talk to you about this anymore,

15:10.431 --> 15:13.855
but thank you for being there
for me when no one else was.

15:13.856 --> 15:14.881
It means a lot.

15:14.882 --> 15:16.309
Well, grief has a way of bubbling up

15:16.310 --> 15:17.613
when you least expect it.

15:21.056 --> 15:23.128
Look, I... Better get back to work.

15:23.712 --> 15:25.098
Thank you for stopping by.

15:25.099 --> 15:26.232
Of course.

15:30.144 --> 15:31.142
[Glenn whistles]

15:32.053 --> 15:34.197
Everything we've been working towards.

15:34.198 --> 15:35.494
Howie V: Okay, before
we bring the baffles in,

15:35.844 --> 15:37.799
let's let you rehearse
one, get a feel for it.

15:38.534 --> 15:39.901
- Juliette: Okay.
- All right.

15:39.902 --> 15:40.967
Hi, guys.

15:40.968 --> 15:43.190
Allow me to escort you to
your throne, your highness.

15:43.191 --> 15:44.884
You ready to step into your future?

15:45.311 --> 15:47.026
[Sighs] Let's hope so.

15:47.027 --> 15:48.277
[Chuckles]

15:49.432 --> 15:50.504
[Instruments tuning]

15:52.113 --> 15:54.200
Hello? Hello, hello?

15:54.839 --> 15:56.034
That sounds good.

15:59.223 --> 16:01.234
