♪ Hey ♪

17:09.089 --> 17:10.473
♪ Well, it's gonna take more ♪

17:10.474 --> 17:13.220
♪ Gonna take more, gonna take more ♪

17:13.221 --> 17:15.121
♪ To pull me under ♪

17:15.122 --> 17:17.194
♪ Gonna take more, gonna take more ♪

17:17.195 --> 17:21.246
♪ Gonna take more than
that to pull me under ♪

17:21.247 --> 17:23.905
♪ This time, it's goodbye, trouble ♪

17:23.906 --> 17:26.678
♪ I feel the light at
the end of this tunnel ♪

17:33.671 --> 17:36.706
Yeah, most folks just kind
of take what I can give them

17:36.707 --> 17:38.747
and not offer a lot in return.

17:38.748 --> 17:39.705
Oh.

17:39.706 --> 17:41.255
Thanks for looking at my lyrics.

17:41.256 --> 17:43.336
No, thank you for showing them to me.

17:43.337 --> 17:45.865
I'm really... like, after this is done,

17:45.866 --> 17:48.957
you should lock yourself away
and work on your own music.

17:48.958 --> 17:50.550
I know. I should.

17:51.744 --> 17:53.487
<i>But then I'll miss working with you.</i>

17:53.792 --> 17:54.715
[Chuckles]

17:54.716 --> 17:56.806
Well, luckily, we got
a whole album to finish.

17:56.807 --> 17:57.775
Yeah.

17:59.207 --> 18:01.045
Mm. What are you doing?

18:01.359 --> 18:03.892
I'm... I'm kissing you. But
if you don't want me to...

18:04.716 --> 18:06.657
I don't think it's a very good idea.

18:07.107 --> 18:08.400
That's all.

18:09.174 --> 18:10.796
I'm gonna get myself home.

18:17.163 --> 18:18.318
Well, I thank y'all for being here.

18:18.319 --> 18:20.374
Look, um, I thought we'd
start off with "Like New."

18:20.375 --> 18:21.384
Can you pass those out?

18:21.385 --> 18:23.436
Uh, "Playin' Tricks."
"You're the Kind of Trouble."

18:23.437 --> 18:24.777
Zoey, you know all those choruses?

18:24.778 --> 18:25.603
Yeah.

18:25.604 --> 18:26.457
All right, don't be shy.

18:26.458 --> 18:28.122
All right. [Feedback]

18:28.123 --> 18:30.885
Hey, tonight, you're in for a real treat.

18:31.317 --> 18:34.671
We were able to book this
very, very special guest

18:34.672 --> 18:36.116
at the last minute tonight.

18:36.483 --> 18:40.391
Put your hands together
for the one and only,

18:40.755 --> 18:42.477
The Wild Feathers!

18:42.478 --> 18:43.892
[Cheers and applause]

18:43.893 --> 18:44.803
Hey, wait, wait, wait, wait, wait.

18:44.804 --> 18:46.792
I'm Deacon Claybourne.
Um, I'm the 10:30 slot.

18:46.793 --> 18:47.939
I'm supposed to be playing at 10:30.

18:47.940 --> 18:49.289
<i>Oh, you did have the 10:30 slot,</i>

18:49.290 --> 18:51.723
but I had to rejigger the lineup
once The Wild Feathers came in.

18:51.724 --> 18:52.929
Well, you couldn't tell me that?

18:52.930 --> 18:54.284
I'll have you guys on by midnight.

18:54.285 --> 18:55.171
[Intro plays] Midnight?

18:55.172 --> 18:58.192
Hey, nobody's gonna be here
listening to music at midnight!

18:58.193 --> 19:00.378
Sorry, man. Take it or leave it.

19:00.379 --> 19:02.318
[The Wild Feathers' "Got it Wrong" plays]

19:04.443 --> 19:05.714
Let's get the hell out of here.

19:06.140 --> 19:07.267
They're pushing us all the way back

19:07.268 --> 19:08.315
to almost closing time

19:08.316 --> 19:10.522
'cause they got these...
Tail Feathers here tonight.

19:10.523 --> 19:11.549
<i>Wild Feathers.</i>

19:11.550 --> 19:12.863
You know what? Don't.

19:12.864 --> 19:14.598
It's bad enough I dragged
y'all all the way out here,

19:14.599 --> 19:16.691
but I draw the line at lack of respect.

19:16.692 --> 19:18.396
Hey, don't cancel on account of us.

19:18.397 --> 19:19.743
We don't care what time we go on.

19:20.295 --> 19:21.522
You really want to play?

19:21.523 --> 19:22.389
Yeah.

19:22.390 --> 19:24.515
Hey, I'm doing my first
gig with Deacon Claybourne.

19:24.516 --> 19:25.612
Who gets to say that?

19:25.613 --> 19:26.793
We're not leaving.

19:28.928 --> 19:29.998
All right.

19:30.637 --> 19:32.186
We stay, and we play.

19:33.026 --> 19:35.838
♪ Don't believe what you hear ♪

19:37.176 --> 19:39.840
♪ It's all right, baby ♪

19:40.364 --> 19:42.632
♪ 'Cause I need you near ♪

19:42.633 --> 19:45.269
Babe, I'm not letting you come
back from Australia for this.

19:46.186 --> 19:48.033
Because it's too far.

19:48.409 --> 19:51.029
I'm fine. I promise you... I'm fine.

19:51.030 --> 19:53.161
And there's nothing you can do here.

19:53.162 --> 19:54.821
All right, yeah. I'll talk
to you in a little bit.

19:54.822 --> 19:56.160
Thanks, babe. Bye.

19:57.575 --> 19:58.522
Hey.

19:58.523 --> 19:59.559
Thought you might be hungry.

19:59.560 --> 20:00.910
Lasagna for you and the girls.

20:01.326 --> 20:03.114
Looks like you got plenty of food, though.

20:03.115 --> 20:05.027
Ohh, I'm so sorry, Ray.

20:05.513 --> 20:07.250
I went through this with my mom.

20:07.251 --> 20:08.697
- I know you did.
- It was rough.

20:08.698 --> 20:10.511
You know, there's... there's
just no way around it.

20:10.512 --> 20:12.296
You lose a parent, you
lose a part of yourself.

20:12.730 --> 20:14.624
Yeah. You do. [Sighs]

20:14.625 --> 20:15.967
I-I rescheduled your meetings.

20:15.968 --> 20:17.186
I pushed back your press events,

20:17.187 --> 20:20.058
so you are free and clear until
you are ready to dive back in.

20:20.059 --> 20:22.232
All right, well, the funeral's
just gonna be real simple...

20:22.233 --> 20:23.358
family and friends.

20:23.359 --> 20:24.515
Of course, I'd love for you to come.

20:24.516 --> 20:26.347
Yeah. Of course I'll be
there. I wouldn't miss it.

20:26.348 --> 20:27.537
You gonna do a song?

20:27.538 --> 20:28.969
No. No.

20:28.970 --> 20:30.202
There's not gonna be any singing.

20:34.576 --> 20:35.798
[Indistinct conversations]

20:36.399 --> 20:38.955
["Like New" plays]

