♪ It'd take about a million midnights ♪

20:44.914 --> 20:48.812
♪ And a good, long whiskey rain ♪

20:49.870 --> 20:51.921
♪ It's gonna take a hurricane ♪

20:51.922 --> 20:53.980
♪ Skies so blue ♪

20:53.981 --> 20:56.323
♪ And I'll be just like new ♪

21:00.300 --> 21:04.819
♪ It might take every inch of Texas ♪

21:05.684 --> 21:09.849
♪ And the dark side of the moon ♪

21:10.569 --> 21:14.409
♪ Gonna find a place
I ain't missing you ♪

21:14.410 --> 21:17.525
♪ And I'll be just like new ♪

21:18.771 --> 21:21.245
♪ When the sun stops shining ♪

21:21.246 --> 21:23.766
♪ When the liars quit lying ♪

21:23.767 --> 21:28.027
♪ When I finally face the truth ♪

21:28.903 --> 21:31.495
♪ I'll be pushing up roses ♪

21:31.496 --> 21:35.769
♪ Gonna start getting over you ♪

21:37.669 --> 21:41.078
♪ I'll be just like new ♪

21:41.079 --> 21:43.467
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh ♪

21:43.468 --> 21:46.298
[Cheers and applause] ♪ ooh, ooh, ooh ♪

21:49.882 --> 21:51.948
[Soft piano music plays]

21:51.949 --> 21:53.044
[Glenn sighs]

21:53.045 --> 21:54.245
That was Bucky.

21:54.673 --> 21:55.838
Rayna's father died.

21:56.299 --> 21:57.588
What? When?

21:57.589 --> 21:59.883
Earlier today. Heart attack.

22:00.916 --> 22:01.839
You're kidding me.

22:01.840 --> 22:04.231
I'll text her, find
out when the funeral is.

22:04.232 --> 22:05.602
Oh, the plans are still up in the air,

22:05.603 --> 22:08.138
but it's gonna be small
and private, anyway.

22:08.139 --> 22:10.761
And besides, we're on
Howie V time here, so...

22:11.604 --> 22:12.928
There she is.

22:12.929 --> 22:13.909
Hey.

22:13.910 --> 22:15.215
[Chuckles] [Clears throat]

22:15.216 --> 22:17.647
So, I've been talking to my
contacts back in Nashville,

22:17.957 --> 22:19.098
to let them know the two of you

22:19.099 --> 22:20.250
are gonna be working together.

22:20.251 --> 22:21.288
Thank you, Val.

22:21.289 --> 22:23.041
Uh, yeah, I've been
talking to my friends, too.

22:23.042 --> 22:24.996
I slipped a copy of the track
that we laid down earlier

22:24.997 --> 22:28.731
to Interscope, Sony, Warner...
hyping up my next big thing.

22:28.732 --> 22:30.146
That's amazing. Thank you.

22:30.147 --> 22:31.545
Well, if we're gonna take over the world,

22:31.546 --> 22:33.774
we got to start thinking
bigger than Nashville, right?

22:33.775 --> 22:37.064
In fact, you should probably
consider moving out here to L.A.

22:37.065 --> 22:37.851
[Gulps]

22:38.358 --> 22:40.703
Y'all drive a little too much for my taste.

22:40.704 --> 22:41.717
[Chuckles] [Chuckles]

22:42.984 --> 22:44.752
Seems like the right
move, though, you know?

22:44.753 --> 22:46.932
New look, new home, new you.

22:47.316 --> 22:48.446
Right?

22:48.447 --> 22:50.048
I mean, all we got to do is
strip that last little bit

22:50.049 --> 22:52.157
of country twang out of
your voice, and we're golden.

22:52.158 --> 22:54.132
The transformation will be complete.

22:54.453 --> 22:56.336
Now, it's not a done deal yet,

22:56.337 --> 22:57.835
but I've been trying to get my good friend

22:57.836 --> 23:01.566
<i>over at Rolling Stone
to put you on the cover.</i>

23:01.567 --> 23:03.227
And he's dragging his feet saying yes,

23:03.600 --> 23:04.478
so I thought I'd throw

23:04.479 --> 23:06.527
a little photo shoot of
my own together tomorrow,

23:06.528 --> 23:08.557
try to convince him of
the genius of the idea.

23:08.879 --> 23:10.685
What do you say? Sound good?

23:11.049 --> 23:13.519
<i>To the cover of Rolling Stone.</i>

23:13.520 --> 23:14.986
<i>To the cover of the Rolling Stone.</i>

23:19.583 --> 23:21.015
[Cheers and applause]

23:21.339 --> 23:22.481
Thank you very much.

23:22.482 --> 23:24.741
We appreciate y'all hanging
out for the midnight show.

23:25.216 --> 23:27.290
We sure hope we get to
play for you again sometime.

23:27.291 --> 23:28.259
Take care.

23:28.668 --> 23:30.405
[Cheering continues]

23:33.328 --> 23:36.609
By "sometime," I hope you
mean back here and often...

23:37.046 --> 23:37.994
As a headliner. [Chuckles]

23:38.795 --> 23:39.608
[Cellphone chimes]

23:39.609 --> 23:40.663
Well, thanks, man. That'd be great.

23:40.664 --> 23:41.666
<i>Yeah, that would be great.</i>

23:41.667 --> 23:43.469
Um... Uh, I'm sorry.

23:43.470 --> 23:44.705
There's been a death in the family.

23:45.006 --> 23:46.909
Here, um... Can you take my guitar for me?

23:46.910 --> 23:47.846
Yeah.

23:47.847 --> 23:49.660
<i>- Thank you.
- Yeah. Thank you.</i>

23:51.091 --> 23:52.546
[Cellphone buzzing]

24:00.641 --> 24:01.549
Hey.

24:01.550 --> 24:03.658
I just got Maddie's text about Lamar.

24:03.659 --> 24:04.632
Ray, I'm just...

24:06.513 --> 24:07.992
I'm sorry.

24:07.993 --> 24:09.110
How you doing?

24:09.603 --> 24:11.465
Oh, you know, it sucks.

24:12.204 --> 24:13.404
Not gonna lie.

24:13.405 --> 24:14.982
Maddie sounded real teary on the phone.

24:14.983 --> 24:16.938
I'm just an hour away.

24:16.939 --> 24:18.610
I was at a gig, but I can
get out of here real quick

24:18.611 --> 24:20.050
and get over to you if you want.

24:20.051 --> 24:21.233
Oh, no. Don't do that.

24:21.234 --> 24:22.918
Listen, I just got those girls down.

24:23.965 --> 24:25.326
They've been crying all day.

24:25.327 --> 24:27.089
I don't want to get them
all stirred up again.

24:27.090 --> 24:29.058
Okay. What can I do?

24:29.059 --> 24:30.576
Honestly, nothing.

24:30.577 --> 24:33.420
Listen, I know Teddy and I
have been having our problems,

24:33.421 --> 24:37.057
but I just... I think I
should be at that funeral.

24:37.058 --> 24:39.058
Think I should be there
for you and the girls.

24:39.059 --> 24:40.761
I wouldn't have it any other way.

24:42.022 --> 24:43.208
You're family.

24:43.732 --> 24:46.365
Ray, I know you got other
shoulders to cry on, but...

24:46.366 --> 24:49.462
You know, I'm not crying. I'm fine.

24:49.463 --> 24:51.189
You're not fine, okay?

24:51.190 --> 24:52.662
I know you're not fine.

24:52.663 --> 24:53.659
I'm fine.

24:53.660 --> 24:54.906
I'll talk to you.

25:04.634 --> 25:07.091
♪ Come hell, come high water ♪

25:07.092 --> 25:10.282
♪ You push on me, I'm
gonna push back harder ♪

25:10.283 --> 25:11.977
[Howie V shouting indistinctly]

25:11.978 --> 25:13.672
♪ I got a whole lot more
than a little bit left ♪

25:14.001 --> 25:16.880
That's it! Great! ♪ Oh,
so don't put dirt... ♪

25:16.881 --> 25:18.790
Yes, yes, yes! Beautiful, beautiful.

25:18.791 --> 25:20.181
Fantastic. Okay, we got that.

25:20.182 --> 25:21.957
Let's get some natural light in here.

25:21.958 --> 25:23.474
Take five for touch-ups.

25:23.475 --> 25:24.572
Thank you.

25:25.021 --> 25:26.469
Here you go. [Sighs]

25:27.818 --> 25:29.299
What do you think?

25:29.300 --> 25:31.940
It's really... Interesting.

25:31.941 --> 25:33.287
<i>- You don't like it?
- Do you?</i>

25:34.032 --> 25:36.064
I... is it too weird?

25:36.065 --> 25:38.558
<i>I mean, it is a little
out there, even for you.</i>

25:38.889 --> 25:40.867
But given your relationship with Rayna

25:40.868 --> 25:42.536
and what's going on with her, just...

25:42.537 --> 25:45.253
Yeah. Yeah. I was worried
about that. I'm not sure.

25:45.254 --> 25:46.196
Look, I mean, if you're not comfortable,

25:46.197 --> 25:47.367
we can change things up.

25:47.368 --> 25:48.839
I'll talk to Howie. We will work it out.

25:49.157 --> 25:50.572
We're just getting going
here. I'll talk to Howie.

25:50.573 --> 25:51.714
Guys, thank you. That's enough. Thank you.

25:52.419 --> 25:54.250
I mean, damn. [Chuckles]

25:54.251 --> 25:56.506
This just might be my best work ever.

25:56.507 --> 25:57.960
Let's get you back in
there for round 2, huh?

25:57.961 --> 25:59.060
Just... just hang on a second.

25:59.061 --> 26:00.043
Listen.

26:00.044 --> 26:01.843
- I'm overthinking it.
- Are you?

26:01.844 --> 26:03.401
- It's just different.
- Okay.

26:03.402 --> 26:04.406
- It's good.
- All right.

26:04.407 --> 26:05.224
Well, let me know.

26:06.451 --> 26:07.624
Howie V: All right, all right.

26:07.625 --> 26:09.108
It's... it's a little extreme.

26:09.109 --> 26:10.462
That's how we make history, right?

26:10.463 --> 26:11.541
By making noise.

26:11.971 --> 26:13.591
You know what? There is, um...

26:13.592 --> 26:15.281
There's this great little
coffee shop around the corner.

26:15.282 --> 26:16.928
Maybe you could make a
quick run for everyone?

26:16.929 --> 26:17.955
Thanks.

26:19.010 --> 26:21.123
I know that you said that you
would take care of everything,

26:21.124 --> 26:24.259
but I stopped by daddy's and
picked out a few of his things.

26:24.569 --> 26:27.820
Good. The funeral director
was just asking me about that.

26:28.398 --> 26:30.421
Well, this is one of his favorites.

26:30.422 --> 26:31.754
He wore it on special occasions,

26:31.755 --> 26:33.099
and he really loved this tie

26:33.100 --> 26:34.722
that the girls gave him last Christmas.

26:35.608 --> 26:36.981
[Scoffs]

26:36.982 --> 26:40.099
I think if I had it my way,
we'd bury him in a pine box...

26:40.405 --> 26:42.074
Nowhere near mom, so...

26:42.873 --> 26:44.549
Trust me... I know exactly how you feel,

26:44.550 --> 26:46.339
given everything that
you've learned about him

26:46.340 --> 26:50.305
in the last couple days,
but... He was still our father.

26:50.306 --> 26:53.585
Tandy, he basically behaved
this way his entire life.

26:53.890 --> 26:56.178
We just found out about
the worst of it at the end.

26:57.027 --> 26:58.974
I was mad at him, too.

26:58.975 --> 27:01.953
I-I... for mom, for Peggy, for everything.

27:01.954 --> 27:04.034
But I wanted him punished, not dead.

27:05.541 --> 27:08.027
<i>You can't tell me that
you don't feel anything.</i>

27:08.028 --> 27:10.103
I feel plenty.

27:10.805 --> 27:13.098
His being dead just
doesn't change any of that.

27:14.134 --> 27:16.892
Bury him in whatever the
hell you want. I don't care.

27:23.614 --> 27:25.639
- Hey, you.
- Scarlett: Hey.

27:25.640 --> 27:26.991
I didn't even know anyone was here.

27:26.992 --> 27:28.901
Oh, just... I was trying
to catch up on some sleep.

27:28.902 --> 27:30.910
Oh, I'll bet. You've been
working such crazy hours.

27:30.911 --> 27:32.854
Your Uncle said you're like
ships passing in the night.

27:32.855 --> 27:34.011
[Chuckles] Yeah. I know.

27:35.367 --> 27:36.472
Everything okay?

27:37.278 --> 27:38.304
Yeah, yeah.

27:38.305 --> 27:39.913
Have you seen Deacon? Where is he?

27:39.914 --> 27:41.192
He's at the Bluebird, getting ready.

27:41.193 --> 27:42.185
I have dinner with a client,

27:42.186 --> 27:43.965
but, um, I may swing by afterwards.

27:43.966 --> 27:44.804
He's playing?

27:44.805 --> 27:46.289
Yeah, he got his old Thursday slot back.

27:47.584 --> 27:49.123
[Chuckling] He forgot to tell me.

27:56.633 --> 27:58.368
Where'd you go? Why'd you leave?

27:59.249 --> 28:00.790
I... Don't belong here.

28:01.612 --> 28:02.870
What are you talking about?

28:02.871 --> 28:03.759
Look...

28:04.590 --> 28:06.748
It's been an incredible journey with you.

28:07.612 --> 28:08.786
That county fair...

28:08.787 --> 28:11.402
You had such a big voice for
someone so young, remember?

28:11.403 --> 28:12.463
Whoa. What's going on?

28:12.464 --> 28:15.120
And I am so proud of how far you've come.

28:16.537 --> 28:19.815
But... It's time for me to step away.

28:19.816 --> 28:21.263
What are you talking about?

28:21.711 --> 28:22.718
Listen, you are on the verge

28:22.719 --> 28:24.918
of doing something truly incredible here.

28:24.919 --> 28:26.750
Howie V's gonna take you all the way.

28:26.751 --> 28:28.565
I can't be the deadweight holding you back.

28:28.566 --> 28:30.959
You are not deadweight.
You're not quitting.

28:30.960 --> 28:32.323
- Listen.
- It's not happening.

28:32.324 --> 28:34.065
I think that, despite all of
our battles over the years,

28:34.456 --> 28:37.196
you never doubted that I had
your best interests at heart.

28:37.197 --> 28:38.414
And that's still true.

28:38.731 --> 28:39.777
And that...

28:41.225 --> 28:42.815
That will always be true.

28:44.803 --> 28:46.762
But I got to get out of the way

28:46.763 --> 28:48.507
and let you go be a superstar.

28:49.865 --> 28:53.507
So, um, Lamar's, uh, funeral is tomorrow,

28:53.508 --> 28:54.779
and if you're finished with Howie V,

28:55.801 --> 28:58.006
your jet's at the airport
whenever you're ready to go.

29:10.108 --> 29:12.276
[Cheers and applause]

29:13.552 --> 29:14.542
Thank you.

29:15.289 --> 29:16.455
Evening, everybody.

29:16.456 --> 29:20.646
Um, as I'm sure you know, a dear
member of our Bluebird family

29:20.647 --> 29:23.387
is tonight mourning the loss of her father.

29:24.099 --> 29:25.611
If we could all just
bow our heads a moment,

29:25.612 --> 29:28.673
send some prayers towards
Rayna Jaymes and her daughters.

29:32.147 --> 29:33.491
Thank you for that.

29:34.049 --> 29:35.371
All right, before we kick this off,

29:35.372 --> 29:37.590
there's a few folks here
that, uh, I wanted to thank.

29:38.462 --> 29:41.146
Uh, Gunnar, Avery, Zoey...

29:41.460 --> 29:43.154
could y'all come up here a second?

29:43.155 --> 29:44.911
[Applause]

29:45.878 --> 29:47.262
Um, what's happening?

29:47.263 --> 29:49.284
I'm not sure, but you might
want to lose the apron.

29:49.285 --> 29:50.447
Uh, this is the younger crowd

29:50.448 --> 29:52.532
that I've been hanging out
with a little bit recently,

29:52.533 --> 29:54.247
and, uh, last night, along with the help

29:54.248 --> 29:56.565
of their, uh, very
talented friends over here,

29:56.566 --> 29:57.704
they saved my butt.

29:58.059 --> 29:59.142
Uh, but more than that,

29:59.143 --> 30:01.935
they reminded me what it is
I love about making music.

30:02.644 --> 30:04.978
It's not about the fame or being a big star

30:06.002 --> 30:08.856
or how bad your time slot is at the show.

30:08.857 --> 30:09.910
[Chuckles]

30:10.373 --> 30:12.831
It's about coming together
and bringing people together

30:13.677 --> 30:15.920
and making that sweet, sweet sound.

30:15.921 --> 30:18.021
I spoke with the guys here,
and what we'd like to do is

30:18.022 --> 30:19.146
I'd like to take these instruments,

30:19.147 --> 30:20.443
turn them over to them,

30:20.444 --> 30:22.364
let them start off this
night with one of theirs.

30:22.365 --> 30:23.381
What do you think about that?

30:23.382 --> 30:24.626
[Cheers and applause] Yep. All right.

30:26.010 --> 30:26.939
Zoey: Wow.

30:27.268 --> 30:28.565
Gunnar: Thanks, man.

30:32.975 --> 30:36.907
♪ That all changed ♪

30:37.615 --> 30:39.661
♪ Under the downtown neon lights ♪

30:40.251 --> 30:42.301
♪ That's where you caught my eye ♪

30:42.628 --> 30:44.650
♪ You got me all worked up ♪

30:44.651 --> 30:46.603
♪ I ain't leaving without your love ♪

30:47.063 --> 30:49.540
♪ It's obvious we both know ♪

30:49.541 --> 30:51.769
♪ This won't end tomorrow ♪

30:51.770 --> 30:53.669
♪ Tonight ain't long enough ♪

30:53.670 --> 30:55.880
♪ I ain't leaving without your love ♪

30:55.881 --> 30:58.418
♪ I ain't leaving without your love ♪

31:02.371 --> 31:03.566
They're great.

31:05.004 --> 31:06.749
<i>I think you mean he's great.</i>

31:08.369 --> 31:09.592
♪ Jukebox dies just in time ♪

31:09.593 --> 31:11.757
And he is. Do yourself a
favor. Don't lose that one.

31:12.517 --> 31:14.648
♪ Last call, last song ♪

31:14.649 --> 31:17.380
♪ Give me one more dance ♪

31:17.381 --> 31:20.693
♪ One more dance ♪

31:20.998 --> 31:22.419
Hey, how's Rayna?

31:22.420 --> 31:24.036
I called her and left her a message,

31:24.037 --> 31:25.542
and I didn't hear back from her.

31:26.660 --> 31:28.544
She's fronting like she's okay, but...

31:30.131 --> 31:31.346
I'm worried.

31:32.804 --> 31:35.637
Well, if my own personal
experience can shed any light...

31:35.638 --> 31:36.867
♪ Tonight ain't long enough ♪

31:37.168 --> 31:38.548
You probably should be.

31:39.263 --> 31:41.578
♪ I ain't leaving without your love ♪

31:49.156 --> 31:52.880
♪ Don't put dirt on my grave just yet ♪

31:53.416 --> 31:54.660
♪ No ♪

31:54.661 --> 31:59.062
♪ Don't put dirt on my grave just yet ♪

31:59.443 --> 32:00.313
[Click]

32:01.735 --> 32:03.468
That is something else.

32:04.076 --> 32:05.460
What do you think?

32:05.461 --> 32:07.879
I mean, it's huge. It's epic.

32:07.880 --> 32:09.141
You should be really happy.

32:10.262 --> 32:13.620
Yeah, I would be if Glenn
wasn't such a buzzkill about it.

32:13.621 --> 32:16.308
Yeah, it's kind of weird how
he just up and quit like that.

32:17.119 --> 32:18.234
You want to talk about it?

32:19.269 --> 32:20.551
No.

32:20.552 --> 32:24.719
I do want to talk about you up
on the stage at the Bluebird.

32:25.086 --> 32:27.212
You looked like you
were having so much fun.

32:27.213 --> 32:30.134
Well, I was in good company, you know?

32:30.135 --> 32:32.699
Just playing with friends
that get me and my music.

32:32.700 --> 32:34.906
And... Makes all the difference.

32:38.894 --> 32:40.526
Don't much like being hung up on.

32:41.681 --> 32:42.766
I know.

32:45.153 --> 32:46.813
I told you... I'm fine.

32:47.586 --> 32:49.357
Well, you can cut that out right now.

32:50.323 --> 32:51.286
This is too damn big

32:51.287 --> 32:53.167
to just shove down and
deal with later, Rayna.

32:54.097 --> 32:55.096
Talk to me.

32:56.444 --> 32:58.357
- Tea?
- No, I don't want tea.

32:58.358 --> 32:59.457
I want you to talk, all right?

32:59.458 --> 33:00.917
If anybody understands how complicated

33:00.918 --> 33:03.389
your relationship with Lamar was, it's me.

33:03.390 --> 33:05.139
- You don't.
- I don't?

33:05.140 --> 33:05.991
Nope.

33:05.992 --> 33:07.385
[Scoffs] Please. I was there.

33:07.386 --> 33:08.914
You haven't been here in a long time.

33:12.869 --> 33:17.568
Last time I saw my daddy,
I told him... He was dead to me.

33:17.569 --> 33:19.054
And I meant it.

33:19.055 --> 33:21.308
<i>Funny thing is, a few hours later, he was.</i>

33:22.454 --> 33:25.363
- I'm sorry, Ray.
- I don't know that I am.

33:25.364 --> 33:26.484
Come on, now.

33:26.863 --> 33:29.265
I found out he was involved
in my mother's death.

33:30.147 --> 33:31.106
No.

33:31.107 --> 33:33.518
Yeah. Drove her off the road.

33:34.719 --> 33:36.295
[Sighing] Oh, my God.

33:37.059 --> 33:40.163
And other... Horrible things

33:40.164 --> 33:43.261
I-I'm not even gonna... Tell you about.

33:44.202 --> 33:45.016
[Sighs]

33:45.017 --> 33:46.520
Of course, Tandy knew the whole time.

33:47.539 --> 33:49.188
Didn't bother to tell me.

33:49.189 --> 33:51.957
The girls keep asking
why aunt Tandy moved out.

33:52.910 --> 33:54.970
Come from a family full of liars.

33:54.971 --> 33:55.910
[Sighs]

33:55.911 --> 33:56.971
I'm just sorry, Ray.

33:58.633 --> 33:59.856
And I know you're angry,

33:59.857 --> 34:01.311
but maybe you just got to
leave a little room to think

34:01.684 --> 34:04.820
maybe they were just hiding some
of that truth to protect you.

34:05.319 --> 34:06.850
No, they were lying.

34:06.851 --> 34:09.913
Sometimes, people do the wrong
things for the right reasons.

34:11.549 --> 34:13.070
They don't intend to harm you.

34:13.071 --> 34:14.713
They just... they're
trying to make the best

34:14.714 --> 34:16.458
of a bad situation.

34:16.458 --> 34:17.645
Yeah.

34:18.317 --> 34:20.141
Sometimes, people do that.

34:21.937 --> 34:23.436
But not this time.

34:29.347 --> 34:30.889
Hey, I got your text.

34:31.315 --> 34:32.283
You okay?

34:32.284 --> 34:33.945
No. No, I'm not.

34:33.946 --> 34:35.063
[Breathes shakily]

34:35.478 --> 34:37.353
I thought I could put it behind me, but...

34:37.355 --> 34:39.536
That if I could just get justice somehow,

34:39.538 --> 34:41.005
that it would be all right.

34:41.005 --> 34:43.270
Right, and then the... the
case against Lamar was dropped.

34:43.271 --> 34:46.539
Exactly. And I couldn't
let him get away with it.

34:46.848 --> 34:48.105
I had to make him pay.

34:48.106 --> 34:49.175
What are you talking about?

34:49.176 --> 34:50.112
[Sighs]

34:50.112 --> 34:54.367
Lamar came here to my office
and confronted me again about,

34:54.869 --> 34:56.735
you know, being a star witness against him.

34:57.813 --> 34:59.643
And I told him that it was Tandy...

35:01.557 --> 35:03.283
That it was her who had betrayed him.

35:03.728 --> 35:06.699
And I don't know if it was
the shock that was too much,

35:06.700 --> 35:09.170
but the next thing I knew,
he was grabbing his chest.

35:09.171 --> 35:10.731
I'm sure you felt powerless.

35:10.732 --> 35:12.116
No.

35:12.117 --> 35:13.729
I had all the power in that moment.

35:16.877 --> 35:18.522
And I didn't do anything.

35:22.796 --> 35:24.467
I just watched him die.

35:39.115 --> 35:40.303
You just getting in?

35:40.786 --> 35:41.990
Yeah.

35:41.991 --> 35:43.379
Sorry I'm so late.

35:47.616 --> 35:48.866
We need to talk.

35:54.441 --> 35:55.505
[Sighs]

35:56.362 --> 35:57.808
I went over to Rayna's.

35:58.122 --> 35:59.317
[Inhales deeply]

36:01.121 --> 36:02.057
Okay.

36:02.534 --> 36:05.958
Yeah, she's just, you know,
like, shut down and numb,

36:06.930 --> 36:08.735
'cause she's so damn angry.

36:10.725 --> 36:12.004
Maddie's a wreck.

36:14.028 --> 36:17.753
I just feel like I should go to
that memorial service tomorrow,

36:17.754 --> 36:18.903
like I should be there.

36:19.294 --> 36:20.620
That's a good idea.

36:22.991 --> 36:25.276
It's important to be
there for people in need.

36:25.890 --> 36:27.418
You were there for me.

36:28.376 --> 36:29.581
[Sighs]

36:31.100 --> 36:32.222
[Smooches]

36:46.353 --> 36:50.589
Officiant: As we mourn the loss
of Lamar Wyatt, a dear friend,

36:50.590 --> 36:53.824
loving father, beloved grandfather,

36:54.549 --> 36:58.308
may you find peace in
the words of the Lord.

36:58.872 --> 37:00.542
"Let not your heart be troubled,

37:01.333 --> 37:04.998
"for in my Father's house,
there are many mansions.

37:05.498 --> 37:08.244
And I go to prepare a place for you."

37:08.792 --> 37:12.452
Take comfort in knowing Lamar has not gone,

37:12.453 --> 37:15.780
but gone ahead to rest for eternity

37:15.781 --> 37:20.008
in the loving arms of our
Lord and Savior, Jesus Christ.

37:20.704 --> 37:22.894
Let us say our final goodbyes.

37:26.160 --> 37:27.442
You can go on ahead.

37:40.467 --> 37:41.679
- Hey, guys.
- Hey.

37:41.680 --> 37:43.816
Erika wants to see you
before you start setting up.

37:43.817 --> 37:45.947
Why? Am I in trouble because of last night?

37:45.948 --> 37:47.857
Nope. He is.

37:47.858 --> 37:49.087
What? What'd I do?

37:49.088 --> 37:51.999
Well, now that everyone knows
you sing like a young Diana Ross,

37:52.000 --> 37:54.991
your boyfriend here is gonna have to
write you a bunch of songs to sing.

37:54.992 --> 37:56.943
Hey, come on. You're no slouch
in that department, either.

37:56.944 --> 37:59.994
Yeah, I mean, Juliette Barnes
was a regular old fangirl

37:59.995 --> 38:01.543
watching you up onstage.

38:01.544 --> 38:02.719
Still not talking about it.

38:02.720 --> 38:03.883
Damn it.

38:03.884 --> 38:05.200
Last night was pretty cool, though.

38:05.513 --> 38:07.217
No, I'd say more like "awesome."

38:07.590 --> 38:09.973
I still can't believe
I sang at the Bluebird.

38:09.974 --> 38:11.392
Yes, you did.

38:11.393 --> 38:12.808
Gunnar: You know, I was thinking...

38:12.809 --> 38:14.451
Maybe the three of us could get together

38:14.452 --> 38:16.645
and... Do this again sometime.

38:17.375 --> 38:18.273
What do you think?

38:18.274 --> 38:19.424
What, you mean like a band?

38:19.425 --> 38:21.121
- Let's do it.
- Yeah. You in?

38:22.112 --> 38:23.333
What the hell?

38:23.334 --> 38:24.438
I'm in.

38:28.311 --> 38:29.558
[Cellphone chimes]

38:44.076 --> 38:45.293
[Whistling]

38:49.225 --> 38:50.415
Hey.

38:50.416 --> 38:51.540
Did you sleep here?

38:51.541 --> 38:53.759
Yes... last night, I did. Sorry.

38:54.566 --> 38:55.498
I, uh...

38:56.206 --> 38:57.934
[Chuckles] I'm just gonna go.

38:57.935 --> 38:59.177
No, hold on.

38:59.178 --> 39:00.130
Are you okay?

39:00.584 --> 39:01.826
No, I'm not.

39:01.827 --> 39:03.404
Hey, Scarlett, we're both adults.

39:03.405 --> 39:05.344
Please don't make
something out of the nothing

39:05.345 --> 39:06.429
that didn't even really happen.

39:06.731 --> 39:07.581
[Sighs]

39:08.015 --> 39:09.916
Look, I-I, uh...

39:11.471 --> 39:13.176
Went home to an empty house last night,

39:14.187 --> 39:17.512
so I thought I would go see my
Uncle Deacon at the Bluebird.

39:17.513 --> 39:18.434
He's got a spot there.

39:18.870 --> 39:21.747
And he was there with this girl

39:21.748 --> 39:24.069
I used to be very good friends
with for a really long time...

39:24.490 --> 39:25.272
Mm.

39:25.273 --> 39:27.925
<i>And my ex and also my other ex.</i>

39:28.896 --> 39:30.042
- I get it.
- Yeah.

39:30.955 --> 39:32.766
So, Deacon's up there telling everybody

39:32.767 --> 39:33.648
how great they are

39:34.087 --> 39:36.518
and how much they've
taught him about music,

39:36.519 --> 39:39.184
and, uh, I just didn't want
to be there when he got home,

39:39.527 --> 39:42.438
so I came here to, uh... [Chuckles]

39:42.439 --> 39:45.364
To worry about that nothing
that didn't happen between us.

39:45.365 --> 39:46.671
Are you worried that I would hold

39:47.478 --> 39:49.651
whatever didn't happen against you?

39:49.652 --> 39:51.270
- Ugh.
- That that's gonna affect our work?

39:54.177 --> 39:57.718
Without what we do here... our work...

40:00.443 --> 40:02.065
I don't have anything else.

40:04.485 --> 40:06.800
We're fine. We're... we're good.

40:07.367 --> 40:08.999
I'm still in your corner.

40:09.528 --> 40:11.031
I'm not going anywhere.

40:19.002 --> 40:21.176
I-I-I don't think
we should do this.

40:21.666 --> 40:23.037
Probably not.

40:32.056 --> 40:33.223
[Knock on door]

40:34.624 --> 40:35.597
Hey!

40:35.598 --> 40:36.585
You're not quitting.

40:37.069 --> 40:38.360
Juliette, wait. Hold on a second.

40:38.361 --> 40:40.372
Did you really think that
I'm gonna let you bail

40:40.373 --> 40:41.899
just when things are getting interesting?

40:41.900 --> 40:42.686
Look, I don't want you thinking...

40:42.687 --> 40:44.946
Marshall Evans, Jeff Fordham, Howie V...

40:44.947 --> 40:47.550
They all want me to be
somebody that I'm not.

40:47.551 --> 40:49.443
You are the only person

40:49.444 --> 40:52.639
who has ever stood by
my choice to be myself.

40:53.189 --> 40:55.184
I saw the proofs from the photo shoot.

40:55.185 --> 40:58.688
You never, in a million years,
would have made me do that.

40:59.064 --> 41:00.605
You know who I am.

41:00.965 --> 41:02.916
Yeah, but what about Howie V? I mean...

41:02.917 --> 41:04.976
Ken Inman did not write an article

41:04.977 --> 41:07.195
about some song with an orchestra.

41:07.196 --> 41:09.400
It's a big opportunity to pass up.

41:09.401 --> 41:10.983
Avery's version of that song...

41:12.189 --> 41:14.826
That is what I want the world to hear.

41:14.827 --> 41:18.318
It is not that tween stuff that I hated.

41:18.319 --> 41:19.693
It's got grit.

41:20.732 --> 41:23.523
And besides, Howie V seemed a little eager

41:23.524 --> 41:25.509
to get me away from country
music, and I'm sorry,

41:25.510 --> 41:27.780
but I am not willing to
pull the stakes up yet.

41:28.982 --> 41:30.727
<i>And you shouldn't be, either.</i>

42:05.853 --> 42:06.926
[Gasps]

42:09.023 --> 42:10.244
Aah!

42:11.813 --> 42:12.932
[Wailing]

42:14.337 --> 42:16.040
[Wailing continues]

42:20.423 --> 42:21.771
[Glass breaking]

42:22.825 --> 42:25.181
[Sobbing]

42:34.171 --> 42:35.843
It's got to stop.

42:37.525 --> 42:42.260
[Sobbing] All the lying just has to stop!

42:42.861 --> 42:45.084
Please!

